1
00:00:00,091 --> 00:00:03,0
LUCIFER:
Previously on Lucifer...

2
00:00:03,029 --> 00:00:06,0
So you're the Devil,
and you've left Hell behind

3
00:00:06,021 --> 00:00:08,4
to take a vacation
in Los Angeles.

4
00:00:08,063 --> 00:00:09,5
How could you possibly help me?

5
00:00:09,071 --> 00:00:10,8
I have a certain skill set.

6
00:00:11,005 --> 00:00:12,3
I can be very persuasive
with people.

7
00:00:12,059 --> 00:00:14,5
I got it; the name,
the whole "Lucifer" thing,

8
00:00:14,076 --> 00:00:16,4
and desire is
like your superpower.

9
00:00:16,068 --> 00:00:18,3
(Lucifer groans)
CHLOE: How did you survive

10
00:00:18,056 --> 00:00:19,9
getting shot six times?

11
00:00:20,014 --> 00:00:21,1
Is that your normal reaction

12
00:00:21,031 --> 00:00:22,5
to someone saving your life?

13
00:00:22,073 --> 00:00:23,5
When I see something
I can't explain,

14
00:00:23,077 --> 00:00:25,1
yeah, I look for answers.

15
00:00:25,031 --> 00:00:26,6
Well, I've given you
the answer, Detective.

16
00:00:26,082 --> 00:00:27,9
It's not my fault
you won't accept it.

17
00:00:28,019 --> 00:00:29,0
CHLOE:
What happened with Lucifer?

18
00:00:29,028 --> 00:00:30,4
You don't get it, do you?

19
00:00:30,065 --> 00:00:32,3
He's the Devil! He's the Devil!

20
00:00:32,057 --> 00:00:34,4
LUCIFER: Where's your ex,
Detective Douche?

21
00:00:34,066 --> 00:00:35,4
Hi, Daddy.

22
00:00:35,066 --> 00:00:36,7
Hi, munchkin.

23
00:00:36,091 --> 00:00:37,8
CHLOE: Wow, shocker,
you're late.

24
00:00:38,003 --> 00:00:39,3
Come on, give
me a break.

25
00:00:39,058 --> 00:00:40,9
Right, here's the deal.

26
00:00:41,016 --> 00:00:44,0
We can have as much naked
cuddle time as you desire,

27
00:00:44,025 --> 00:00:46,0
but you're gonna have
to listen to me too.

28
00:00:46,029 --> 00:00:47,7
LINDA: You like
to hide insecurity

29
00:00:47,092 --> 00:00:49,1
in humor, don't you?

30
00:00:49,038 --> 00:00:50,2
What do you think
I'm insecure about?

31
00:00:50,042 --> 00:00:52,1
That you are changing,

32
00:00:52,034 --> 00:00:53,7
that you don't know
what's causing the change.

33
00:00:53,097 --> 00:00:55,4
Or who.

34
00:01:08,023 --> 00:01:10,1
(wind whistling)

35
00:01:26,025 --> 00:01:28,0
Go on.

36
00:01:28,029 --> 00:01:30,4
Go ahead, jump.

37
00:01:33,026 --> 00:01:34,4
You know you want to.

38
00:01:34,063 --> 00:01:36,4
Hmm?

39
00:01:36,063 --> 00:01:39,4
Trust me, it's
a warm welcome.

40
00:01:39,064 --> 00:01:40,7
Won't it hurt?

41
00:01:40,097 --> 00:01:44,1
Oh, there's only
one way to find out.

42
00:01:50,015 --> 00:01:53,6
(cheering, shouting)
♪ All day I was out ♪

43
00:01:53,090 --> 00:01:56,9
♪ Feeling, thinking of you... ♪

44
00:01:57,020 --> 00:01:58,2
Lovely.

45
00:01:58,045 --> 00:02:03,1
♪ Buzzing by myself tonight ♪

46
00:02:03,037 --> 00:02:04,7
♪♪

47
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,1
Sorry.

48
00:02:06,033 --> 00:02:07,8
♪ - Same place ♪
- Excuse me.

49
00:02:08,004 --> 00:02:09,7
♪ Same old rhyme ♪

50
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:14,0
♪ Same troubles
on my mind, too ♪

51
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:16,1
♪ I still changed
and don't know why... ♪

52
00:02:16,034 --> 00:02:17,3
WOMAN: You're the man
of the hour.

53
00:02:17,051 --> 00:02:18,5
Everyone's here
to see you.

54
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:20,6
What's the worst
that can happen?

55
00:02:20,089 --> 00:02:22,7
Come on, have one
drink with me.

56
00:02:22,093 --> 00:02:24,5
I can't, I'm sorry, I'm not
trying to be a buzzkill,

57
00:02:24,077 --> 00:02:26,2
I'm just... I'm not in the
mood to party, all right?

58
00:02:26,043 --> 00:02:28,4
How can you decline
this ravishing siren's

59
00:02:28,069 --> 00:02:30,4
invitation to imbibe?

60
00:02:30,069 --> 00:02:33,8
(chuckles) Well, if L.A.'s
taught me anything,

61
00:02:34,003 --> 00:02:36,2
constant rejections
do build character.

62
00:02:36,044 --> 00:02:37,8
LUCIFER: Sincerely doubt
"constant rejection"

63
00:02:38,003 --> 00:02:39,3
is something you
ever deal with.

64
00:02:39,053 --> 00:02:40,8
(chuckles)

65
00:02:41,003 --> 00:02:42,6
You could learn a thing
or two from this guy.

66
00:02:42,087 --> 00:02:44,6
Oh.
(chuckles)

67
00:02:44,087 --> 00:02:46,3
Witty, charming and wise.

68
00:02:46,054 --> 00:02:47,5
Have you lost your mind?

69
00:02:47,071 --> 00:02:49,1
Do I know you?

70
00:02:49,037 --> 00:02:50,4
Lucifer.

71
00:02:50,067 --> 00:02:51,5
Morningstar.

72
00:02:53,029 --> 00:02:54,4
Right, you're the
club owner guy

73
00:02:54,067 --> 00:02:56,0
who grants people favors.

74
00:02:56,026 --> 00:02:58,5
Yeah, I don't need
anything from you.

75
00:02:58,076 --> 00:03:00,6
Oh, I beg
to differ, Ty.

76
00:03:00,089 --> 00:03:02,1
I have been looking
for you all night.

77
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:04,1
And you are in desperate
need of my help.

78
00:03:04,039 --> 00:03:06,8
Star quarterback,
number-one draft pick,

79
00:03:07,002 --> 00:03:09,9
and yet, for some inexplicable
reason, a virgin.

80
00:03:10,019 --> 00:03:11,8
Look, man, I got all the haters
I need online, all right?

81
00:03:12,002 --> 00:03:14,1
No, no, no, no, no,
I'm not criticizing.

82
00:03:14,036 --> 00:03:15,6
I'm fascinated.

83
00:03:15,082 --> 00:03:18,0
I mean, do you know
how rare you are?

84
00:03:18,024 --> 00:03:20,3
A celebrity virgin
in Los Angeles,

85
00:03:20,057 --> 00:03:22,0
and surrounded by temptation.

86
00:03:22,024 --> 00:03:24,2
I mean, you, Ty, are like

87
00:03:24,049 --> 00:03:26,5
a four-leaf clover
and a unicorn made a baby.

88
00:03:26,074 --> 00:03:28,9
Without, uh, having
sex, of course.

89
00:03:29,012 --> 00:03:30,7
(wry chuckle)

90
00:03:30,092 --> 00:03:32,1
MAN: Aw, thanks,
I appreciate it.

91
00:03:32,038 --> 00:03:33,3
My agent wanted me
to throw this party.

92
00:03:33,054 --> 00:03:34,8
Oh.

93
00:03:35,004 --> 00:03:37,2
- Yeah, he wants me to loosen up.
- He's right.

94
00:03:37,042 --> 00:03:38,8
I've met your type before,

95
00:03:39,009 --> 00:03:40,3
so desperate
to control their lives,

96
00:03:40,059 --> 00:03:41,7
they forget to enjoy it.

97
00:03:41,097 --> 00:03:44,0
So answer me this.

98
00:03:44,026 --> 00:03:47,7
If you were to ever,
you know, let go,

99
00:03:47,093 --> 00:03:50,3
what is it you'd
really want to do?

100
00:03:50,052 --> 00:03:52,2
I, uh...

101
00:03:52,044 --> 00:03:54,4
Yeah.
I...

102
00:03:54,061 --> 00:03:56,5
I want to skip my morning
workout sometimes.

103
00:03:56,077 --> 00:03:58,8
Boring.
Just chill on the couch

104
00:03:59,007 --> 00:03:59,9
and watch Master Chef.

105
00:04:00,011 --> 00:04:01,0
This is the fantasy life

106
00:04:01,024 --> 00:04:02,7
of a postmenopausal housewife.

107
00:04:02,095 --> 00:04:04,9
Come on, Ty, there must
be something deeper.

108
00:04:05,016 --> 00:04:06,5
I, um...

109
00:04:06,078 --> 00:04:08,4
Yeah.

110
00:04:08,058 --> 00:04:10,5
I want to get laid so damn bad.

111
00:04:10,079 --> 00:04:12,7
(laughing):
And there it is.

112
00:04:12,092 --> 00:04:16,0
You got no idea how hard it is
holding out for marriage, man.

113
00:04:16,029 --> 00:04:17,9
Uncomfortably hard, I'm sure.

114
00:04:18,013 --> 00:04:19,9
(both chuckle)

115
00:04:20,013 --> 00:04:21,5
Look, I was going to
with my girl,

116
00:04:21,080 --> 00:04:23,2
but, uh, we broke up.

117
00:04:23,047 --> 00:04:24,2
Oh...

118
00:04:24,047 --> 00:04:25,2
I thought she was gonna be

119
00:04:25,047 --> 00:04:26,9
the mother of my children.

120
00:04:27,018 --> 00:04:28,6
Well, she wants to be
the mother of your children.

121
00:04:28,081 --> 00:04:30,6
Come on, Ty,
it's the fourth quarter,

122
00:04:30,081 --> 00:04:32,8
but you can still
win this game.

123
00:04:33,002 --> 00:04:34,9
I mean, look at her:
death and taxes

124
00:04:35,010 --> 00:04:36,1
are less of a sure thing.

125
00:04:36,036 --> 00:04:37,4
No, I can't.

126
00:04:37,065 --> 00:04:38,7
But you desire her.

127
00:04:38,098 --> 00:04:40,2
Why fight it?

128
00:04:40,049 --> 00:04:43,0
Because my mother
taught me that...

129
00:04:43,028 --> 00:04:45,1
Oh, no, don't-don't bring her
into this; that's disgusting.

130
00:04:45,028 --> 00:04:48,1
Uh... it's about you.

131
00:04:48,033 --> 00:04:49,4
What do you want?

132
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:51,9
Her.

133
00:04:52,016 --> 00:04:54,0
Well, then "carpe diem,"
my friend.

134
00:05:01,071 --> 00:05:03,6
Ah, hello again,
my little cannonball.

135
00:05:03,084 --> 00:05:05,6
Sorry, I didn't
introduce myself earlier.

136
00:05:05,084 --> 00:05:07,3
Lucifer. Morningstar.

137
00:05:07,055 --> 00:05:08,3
Seriously?

138
00:05:08,055 --> 00:05:10,0
Yes, yes.

139
00:05:10,027 --> 00:05:11,8
I'm the Devil, hope you'll
hold it against me.

140
00:05:11,098 --> 00:05:14,9
Lucifer Morningstar,
the guy who owns Lux?

141
00:05:15,014 --> 00:05:16,2
That's me.

142
00:05:16,044 --> 00:05:17,4
(laughing):
No, it's not.

143
00:05:17,061 --> 00:05:19,0
I've seen him before.

144
00:05:19,023 --> 00:05:20,3
His beats are sick.

145
00:05:20,053 --> 00:05:22,0
I very much beg your pardon.

146
00:05:22,024 --> 00:05:23,0
Beats?

147
00:05:23,024 --> 00:05:24,6
Yeah.

148
00:05:24,082 --> 00:05:26,6
He performed at a rap battle
last week in the Valley.

149
00:05:26,086 --> 00:05:29,7
Every single part of that
sentence horrifies me.

150
00:05:29,099 --> 00:05:31,7
It is so gross

151
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,3
that you're pretending
to be someone you're not.

152
00:05:34,054 --> 00:05:37,0
(scoffs)
Even your accent is fake.

153
00:05:38,013 --> 00:05:39,9
(weak coughing)

154
00:05:40,017 --> 00:05:42,3
Me!

155
00:05:42,055 --> 00:05:44,5
(scoffs)

156
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:47,3
♪ Now I'm feeling
like a monster... ♪

157
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:49,0
(chuckles)

158
00:05:49,022 --> 00:05:51,6
Don't mind if I do.

159
00:05:51,089 --> 00:05:53,6
♪ Monster, monster ♪

160
00:05:53,089 --> 00:05:55,6
♪ Ah, ah-ah... ah, ah-ah ♪

161
00:05:55,089 --> 00:05:58,8
♪ Monster, monster ♪

162
00:05:59,002 --> 00:06:00,8
♪ Ah, ah-ah, ah, ah-ah ♪

163
00:06:01,002 --> 00:06:05,5
♪ Monster, monster. ♪

164
00:06:05,074 --> 00:06:07,2
TY:
Lucifer.

165
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:08,5
Wake up.

166
00:06:08,070 --> 00:06:10,5
Something really bad happened.

167
00:06:10,074 --> 00:06:11,9
Well, I hope you enjoyed
every minute of it.

168
00:06:12,020 --> 00:06:13,2
No, no, no, you
don't understand.

169
00:06:13,041 --> 00:06:14,3
Look, I'm freaking out, okay?

170
00:06:14,054 --> 00:06:15,5
Can you just help me, please?

171
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,0
I need that favor.

172
00:06:18,021 --> 00:06:19,7
Right.

173
00:06:24,084 --> 00:06:27,7
♪♪
(gulls screeching)

174
00:06:38,039 --> 00:06:40,7
Mommy, did Daddy
forget to pick me up?

175
00:06:40,094 --> 00:06:44,4
No, monkey, I'm sure
he's just stuck in traffic.

176
00:06:44,061 --> 00:06:46,4
Are you doing
homework?

177
00:06:46,061 --> 00:06:47,7
Um, sort of.

178
00:06:47,095 --> 00:06:49,4
What's the assignment?

179
00:06:51,024 --> 00:06:54,7
Uh, well, I saw Lucifer do
some things I can't explain.

180
00:06:54,095 --> 00:06:56,4
Is Lucifer a magician?

181
00:06:56,066 --> 00:06:58,2
That's sort of what
I'm trying to figure out.

182
00:06:58,046 --> 00:07:00,5
When Daddy gets here,
maybe he can help.

183
00:07:00,079 --> 00:07:02,0
Mm.

184
00:07:02,021 --> 00:07:03,8
Sometimes Daddy helps me
with my homework.

185
00:07:04,009 --> 00:07:06,2
I'm not sure if Daddy has
the answers to these questions.

186
00:07:06,042 --> 00:07:08,5
Why don't you
just ask Lucifer?

187
00:07:08,076 --> 00:07:11,5
Because if he's a magician, then
he won't reveal his secrets.

188
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:14,6
So I have to find out
on my own how Lucifer does...

189
00:07:14,081 --> 00:07:17,6
(cell phone rings, buzzes)
these things that I can't...

190
00:07:17,081 --> 00:07:19,9
explain.

191
00:07:20,014 --> 00:07:21,7
Oh, that can't be him.

192
00:07:21,098 --> 00:07:23,1
(phone beeps on)

193
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:24,6
Decker.

194
00:07:24,082 --> 00:07:27,2
Lucifer, how did you
even get this number?

195
00:07:30,011 --> 00:07:31,9
LUCIFER:
Excuse the mess,

196
00:07:32,012 --> 00:07:34,9
but it's so good of you
to come, Detective Decker.

197
00:07:35,016 --> 00:07:38,9
Thanks for being super-cryptic
in a really unhelpful way.

198
00:07:39,016 --> 00:07:40,8
(chuckles)
What's the emergency?

199
00:07:41,008 --> 00:07:42,6
Well, it's-it's better to
show than tell, really.

200
00:07:50,076 --> 00:07:51,6
I...

201
00:07:54,043 --> 00:07:57,3
♪♪

202
00:08:04,027 --> 00:08:06,0
CORONER: Petechial
hemorrhaging in the eyes.

203
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:07,4
Contusions
on the neck.

204
00:08:07,065 --> 00:08:09,1
Signs of strangulation.

205
00:08:09,032 --> 00:08:11,8
And one of the victim's
fake nails was ripped off.

206
00:08:12,007 --> 00:08:13,2
Signs of struggle.

207
00:08:13,041 --> 00:08:14,9
We got a murder
on our hands.

208
00:08:15,012 --> 00:08:17,2
Thanks.

209
00:08:18,062 --> 00:08:20,4
CHLOE:
So what happened?

210
00:08:20,066 --> 00:08:22,7
TY: Um, well, I woke up early,
'cause my head hurt.

211
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:23,7
I, uh...

212
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,7
I had a hangover.

213
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:27,4
I... I've never
drank before, so...

214
00:08:27,067 --> 00:08:30,0
That's on me. Sorry.

215
00:08:30,030 --> 00:08:31,8
Yeah, so I came down
to get some water,

216
00:08:32,005 --> 00:08:33,3
and that's-that's
when I saw her in the pool.

217
00:08:33,055 --> 00:08:34,4
Did you know her?

218
00:08:34,064 --> 00:08:35,9
Not before last night.

219
00:08:36,018 --> 00:08:37,6
I talked to her for
a little bit.

220
00:08:37,085 --> 00:08:39,6
Her name
was, uh...

221
00:08:39,085 --> 00:08:41,5
Ali, maybe?

222
00:08:41,073 --> 00:08:43,9
I don't know. I mean, I'm having
a hard time remembering.

223
00:08:46,065 --> 00:08:48,1
You think she
accidentally slipped,

224
00:08:48,036 --> 00:08:49,6
fell in the pool
and drowned?

225
00:08:49,086 --> 00:08:51,1
No, I think she was murdered.

226
00:08:51,036 --> 00:08:53,1
Oh, my God, that's...
that's terrible.

227
00:08:53,036 --> 00:08:55,9
So why didn't you call
the police right away?

228
00:08:56,012 --> 00:08:57,5
Well, I told Lucifer.

229
00:08:57,078 --> 00:08:59,1
He said... he said that
he would call the police.

230
00:08:59,033 --> 00:09:00,5
LUCIFER:
And I did.

231
00:09:00,079 --> 00:09:02,0
Detective Decker's
a homicide detective.

232
00:09:02,021 --> 00:09:03,7
She's been very helpful

233
00:09:03,087 --> 00:09:06,6
in the other murders
that I've encountered.

234
00:09:06,088 --> 00:09:09,5
I am not your personal
police concierge.

235
00:09:09,071 --> 00:09:11,1
You are gonna find out
who did this, aren't you?

236
00:09:11,038 --> 00:09:12,7
(inhales)

237
00:09:12,097 --> 00:09:14,4
Of course I am,
because that's my job.

238
00:09:14,068 --> 00:09:15,8
- Right.
- Not because
you want me to.

239
00:09:16,001 --> 00:09:17,4
(scoffs) Right.

240
00:09:17,068 --> 00:09:19,1
First things last:
Do you have any idea

241
00:09:19,035 --> 00:09:20,9
who had contact
with her last night?

242
00:09:21,014 --> 00:09:23,9
Um, no, uh, no, but they asked
me to get the... the guest list.

243
00:09:25,052 --> 00:09:27,5
(quietly):
Oh, geez.

244
00:09:27,077 --> 00:09:28,9
250 guests.

245
00:09:29,011 --> 00:09:29,9
You know what
that means.

246
00:09:30,011 --> 00:09:31,1
Great party.

247
00:09:32,065 --> 00:09:35,1
250 suspects.

248
00:09:36,066 --> 00:09:38,5
Oh. Uh, I'd be careful
with that thing

249
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:40,1
in the guest bedroom.

250
00:09:40,033 --> 00:09:41,3
There's a good chance
you'll go blind.

251
00:09:41,054 --> 00:09:43,0
Unspeakable acts.

252
00:09:43,025 --> 00:09:45,1
Yes, we got a little
carried away. (chuckles)

253
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:47,5
Stop interfering.

254
00:09:47,079 --> 00:09:48,9
I'm helping.

255
00:09:49,013 --> 00:09:50,6
You forget that
my expertise

256
00:09:50,084 --> 00:09:51,8
is finding the right people
to punish, Detective.

257
00:09:52,009 --> 00:09:52,8
It's what I do.

258
00:09:53,009 --> 00:09:54,7
Or, uh, did, at least.

259
00:09:54,092 --> 00:09:56,3
You want to do something?

260
00:09:56,059 --> 00:09:58,3
Then help account for everyone
who was at the party.

261
00:09:58,055 --> 00:10:00,0
- Oh.
- Coroner puts
