00:28:56,002 --> 00:28:57,4
♪... doing what I'm told...♪

782
00:28:57,061 --> 00:28:59,1
(whispering):
Lucifer, what are you doing?

783
00:28:59,036 --> 00:29:00,4
(music playing over speakers)

784
00:29:00,069 --> 00:29:01,8
Hey, Dan, what's going on?

785
00:29:03,078 --> 00:29:05,1
DAN:
I don't know.

786
00:29:05,037 --> 00:29:06,8
They're still talking.

787
00:29:09,066 --> 00:29:11,8
And now she's leaving.

788
00:29:14,050 --> 00:29:15,8
LUCIFER:
Lovely.

789
00:29:17,038 --> 00:29:19,1
What the hell did you do?

790
00:29:19,038 --> 00:29:22,3
I hired the fixer to fix
a problem, like you wanted.

791
00:29:22,055 --> 00:29:23,8
You let her go.
What happened to the plan?

792
00:29:24,001 --> 00:29:25,7
- I made a better one.
- How?

793
00:29:25,093 --> 00:29:27,0
Just sit tight

794
00:29:27,026 --> 00:29:28,3
and we'll all get what we want.

795
00:29:36,015 --> 00:29:38,6
(gasps, grunts)

796
00:29:38,090 --> 00:29:40,6
- Finally!
- (whimpers)

797
00:29:40,086 --> 00:29:43,4
The would-be Prince of Darkness.

798
00:29:43,065 --> 00:29:45,2
Payment due
upon delivery.

799
00:29:45,041 --> 00:29:46,7
(wry laugh)

800
00:29:46,091 --> 00:29:48,9
I'd like to examine
the goods first.

801
00:29:49,020 --> 00:29:50,0
RONNIE:
Your dime.

802
00:29:54,033 --> 00:29:56,2
Right.

803
00:29:56,042 --> 00:29:58,5
Let's see the face
of my impostor.

804
00:30:02,017 --> 00:30:03,4
(Maze laughs)

805
00:30:05,018 --> 00:30:06,8
The resemblance
is uncanny.

806
00:30:09,076 --> 00:30:13,2
It most certainly is not.

807
00:30:13,043 --> 00:30:14,7
(giggling)

808
00:30:14,093 --> 00:30:16,5
How could anyone think
that you were me?

809
00:30:16,077 --> 00:30:18,2
(false British accent): You know
who you're messing with?

810
00:30:19,081 --> 00:30:21,2
I'm Lucifer
freaking Morningstar!

811
00:30:21,044 --> 00:30:22,9
Oh...

812
00:30:23,011 --> 00:30:24,3
Are you now?

813
00:30:24,057 --> 00:30:27,0
Well... you've certainly
been a busy bee,

814
00:30:27,028 --> 00:30:29,0
haven't you, "Lucifer"?

815
00:30:29,028 --> 00:30:30,4
Eh?

816
00:30:30,066 --> 00:30:32,4
Apparently, you've started
a modeling agency,

817
00:30:32,066 --> 00:30:35,2
pitched a Web series.

818
00:30:36,058 --> 00:30:37,7
And I hear
you've also been

819
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,9
very active with the women.

820
00:30:40,013 --> 00:30:41,0
Ladies love me.

821
00:30:41,029 --> 00:30:43,3
What can I say?

822
00:30:43,051 --> 00:30:45,3
It's what they've been saying
that's the trouble.

823
00:30:45,059 --> 00:30:48,2
It seems you're a bit
of a two-pump chump.

824
00:30:48,047 --> 00:30:50,3
Also, a crier afterwards.

825
00:30:50,060 --> 00:30:51,8
That happened one time.

826
00:30:52,001 --> 00:30:54,3
Right. Well, we can't
have you running around

827
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:56,9
cheapening the Lucifer brand,
now, can we?

828
00:30:57,014 --> 00:30:58,2
What do you say, Maze?

829
00:30:58,052 --> 00:31:00,2
Impalement?

830
00:31:00,048 --> 00:31:01,5
MAZE:
Hmm...

831
00:31:01,077 --> 00:31:04,2
Why rush?

832
00:31:04,044 --> 00:31:06,1
- I say the rack.
- Oh.

833
00:31:06,036 --> 00:31:07,6
- Oh!
- Ooh.

834
00:31:07,086 --> 00:31:09,1
That way,

835
00:31:09,036 --> 00:31:10,9
we can really enjoy it.

836
00:31:11,012 --> 00:31:12,8
LUCIFER: Better.
Yes, much better.

837
00:31:13,003 --> 00:31:15,1
Every joint of every limb

838
00:31:15,033 --> 00:31:17,1
dislocated before it's torn off.

839
00:31:17,033 --> 00:31:19,9
No, no, no, no, no-- look, look,
look, I just... I just...

840
00:31:20,017 --> 00:31:22,3
I just wanted to get chicks
and-and free drinks.

841
00:31:22,054 --> 00:31:24,0
Um, really.

842
00:31:25,063 --> 00:31:27,2
(dropping accent):
My name is Justin.

843
00:31:27,047 --> 00:31:28,2
I'm from Sherman Oaks.

844
00:31:28,047 --> 00:31:29,2
(Maze and Lucifer laughing)

845
00:31:29,047 --> 00:31:31,4
Oh, Justin...

846
00:31:31,068 --> 00:31:33,4
the things I'm gonna do to you.

847
00:31:33,064 --> 00:31:34,8
Oh, no, no, no,
I-I'm sorry!

848
00:31:35,001 --> 00:31:36,0
I only came here one time

849
00:31:36,022 --> 00:31:37,8
and I just told some girls

850
00:31:38,010 --> 00:31:39,3
that I owned the place, and...

851
00:31:39,056 --> 00:31:40,8
and that opened
some doors for me

852
00:31:41,006 --> 00:31:42,1
and so I just
started rolling with it.

853
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:44,9
How dare you abscond my name!

854
00:31:45,015 --> 00:31:46,6
Please, don't hurt me.

855
00:31:46,086 --> 00:31:48,0
Please.

856
00:31:48,028 --> 00:31:49,4
LUCIFER:
I'm not gonna hurt you,

857
00:31:49,065 --> 00:31:51,6
Justin,
I'm going to destroy you.

858
00:31:51,087 --> 00:31:54,0
Oh, this is so hot.

859
00:31:54,024 --> 00:31:56,6
It's like you're
punishing yourself.

860
00:32:02,050 --> 00:32:05,3
Seems I could be just, um,

861
00:32:05,055 --> 00:32:06,8
overreacting a bit.

862
00:32:11,051 --> 00:32:13,1
Go.

863
00:32:13,034 --> 00:32:14,3
Go on!

864
00:32:16,051 --> 00:32:17,8
And never sully my name again.

865
00:32:22,015 --> 00:32:23,6
Let's at least take a finger.

866
00:32:23,086 --> 00:32:25,0
We've done enough, Maze.

867
00:32:32,053 --> 00:32:33,7
Pleasure doing business
with you, Lucifer.

868
00:32:33,099 --> 00:32:35,7
Yes, it was, wasn't it?

869
00:32:35,099 --> 00:32:37,7
Which is why I'm going to have
to apologize for my friends.

870
00:32:37,099 --> 00:32:39,0
What friends?

871
00:32:39,020 --> 00:32:40,7
CHLOE:
Ronnie Hillman,

872
00:32:40,096 --> 00:32:42,0
you're under arrest
for kidnapping and assault.

873
00:32:46,096 --> 00:32:48,8
Would you mind
calling my lawyer?

874
00:32:49,005 --> 00:32:50,8
(handcuffs tightening)
Her number's in
my back pocket.

875
00:32:51,001 --> 00:32:52,4
Yeah, sure thing.

876
00:32:52,068 --> 00:32:53,8
I'll tell her
about the kidnapping,

877
00:32:54,009 --> 00:32:55,5
the airtight evidence we have,

878
00:32:55,076 --> 00:32:57,5
the attempted murder
on Debra Macall,

879
00:32:57,072 --> 00:32:59,7
and then when we connect you
to Ali Thornton's murder,

880
00:32:59,093 --> 00:33:01,0
maybe you'll get
a nice injection of drugs,

881
00:33:01,027 --> 00:33:03,0
and you can go to sleep forever.

882
00:33:03,027 --> 00:33:07,3
Hang on-- I had nothing
to do with Ali's murder.

883
00:33:07,057 --> 00:33:11,3
Debra Macall, Ty Huntley's ex,
she's the murderer.

884
00:33:11,057 --> 00:33:13,3
I cared about Ali.

885
00:33:13,053 --> 00:33:15,2
Mm-hmm, here's what I think.

886
00:33:15,049 --> 00:33:17,4
I think you tried to scare Debra
into confessing to Ali's murder,

887
00:33:17,070 --> 00:33:18,8
but Debra didn't do it.

888
00:33:19,004 --> 00:33:20,5
She's got an ironclad alibi.

889
00:33:23,067 --> 00:33:25,5
This is my fault.

890
00:33:25,071 --> 00:33:27,5
Why?

891
00:33:27,071 --> 00:33:31,1
I promised Ali
I would protect her.

892
00:33:31,038 --> 00:33:33,8
All she ever wanted
was to be an actress.

893
00:33:34,005 --> 00:33:35,5
She was gonna leave her mark.

894
00:33:35,072 --> 00:33:36,8
But you know how that goes.

895
00:33:37,001 --> 00:33:40,2
Endless rejection,
she ran out of money.

896
00:33:40,047 --> 00:33:43,2
This was her first gig with me.

897
00:33:43,048 --> 00:33:45,2
She didn't even know
if she could do it.

898
00:33:45,048 --> 00:33:49,6
But I told her... I told her
it was just like acting.

899
00:33:49,082 --> 00:33:52,9
Besides, who doesn't want
to sleep with Ty Huntley?

900
00:33:53,015 --> 00:33:55,6
I thought Ty's agent hired
Ali to sleep with him.

901
00:33:55,082 --> 00:33:58,9
He hired me for a number
three special: blackmail.

902
00:33:59,012 --> 00:34:01,9
Slip him a roofie, get naked,
whip out a selfie stick,

903
00:34:02,012 --> 00:34:03,2
and voilà.

904
00:34:03,045 --> 00:34:04,9
LUCIFER: Why would
he have any desire

905
00:34:05,012 --> 00:34:06,5
to blackmail his
own star client,

906
00:34:06,079 --> 00:34:08,1
a client he's all
about protecting?

907
00:34:08,033 --> 00:34:11,0
Ty's agent told you
that Debra killed Ali.

908
00:34:11,030 --> 00:34:13,7
He did, yeah.

909
00:34:23,064 --> 00:34:25,1
You think Joe's the killer,

910
00:34:25,035 --> 00:34:28,0
that he took things into
his own hands, quite literally.

911
00:34:28,027 --> 00:34:29,5
We don't have any proof.

912
00:34:29,077 --> 00:34:32,5
Right, well, how do you
propose that we get him?

913
00:34:34,019 --> 00:34:35,7
Joe pointed the finger
right at Debra,

914
00:34:35,095 --> 00:34:37,4
painted her as crazy.

915
00:34:37,070 --> 00:34:39,3
It's not that hard a picture
to paint, in her case.

916
00:34:39,053 --> 00:34:41,3
Why was he so certain
she'd make a good suspect?

917
00:34:41,053 --> 00:34:44,4
Maybe he found out
she went to Ty's party.

918
00:34:44,066 --> 00:34:46,6
Maybe he knew she
went to Ty's party.

919
00:35:00,005 --> 00:35:03,5
You are looking
at the future of football.

920
00:35:03,077 --> 00:35:05,7
The American Dream.

921
00:35:05,093 --> 00:35:09,9
Honest, resilient, heroic.

922
00:35:10,019 --> 00:35:12,3
The police tried to pin

923
00:35:12,052 --> 00:35:16,4
the death of that
poor girl on you.

924
00:35:16,061 --> 00:35:19,2
But we kept it
out of the press.

925
00:35:19,041 --> 00:35:22,4
We got you out of jail.

926
00:35:22,070 --> 00:35:24,5
We will always
protect you...

927
00:35:24,079 --> 00:35:27,5
and make you a bigger
star than ever.

928
00:35:27,075 --> 00:35:30,3
This is
Ty Huntley...

929
00:35:30,058 --> 00:35:32,7
rebranded. (laughs)

930
00:35:38,051 --> 00:35:39,4
LUCIFER:
Rebranded, eh?

931
00:35:39,063 --> 00:35:41,0
Does it come
with a new scent?

932
00:35:41,030 --> 00:35:42,2
Free toy inside?

933
00:35:42,047 --> 00:35:44,1
What do you want?

934
00:35:44,039 --> 00:35:46,6
Ty is free on bail.

935
00:35:46,089 --> 00:35:48,8
We have to talk to Ty
down at the station again,

936
00:35:49,006 --> 00:35:50,6
maybe walk him
past a few reporters.

937
00:35:50,081 --> 00:35:52,0
Whoa, hold on, uh,
Joe, what is this?

938
00:35:52,027 --> 00:35:53,7
Oh, come on!
This is ridiculous.

939
00:35:53,098 --> 00:35:56,0
Ty wouldn't
hurt anybody!

940
00:35:56,028 --> 00:35:57,4
What about Debra?

941
00:35:57,061 --> 00:35:58,6
I told you to look into her.

942
00:35:58,090 --> 00:36:00,2
She's the crazy one.

943
00:36:00,049 --> 00:36:01,9
Yes, well, I thought
it was her all along.

944
00:36:02,016 --> 00:36:03,8
I mean, the woman certainly
redefines "intensity."

945
00:36:04,008 --> 00:36:06,4
But Debra was home with a friend
the night of the murder.

946
00:36:06,066 --> 00:36:07,6
What?!

947
00:36:07,083 --> 00:36:09,3
She's lying.

948
00:36:09,058 --> 00:36:10,6
There's no evidence
placing her at the party.

949
00:36:10,083 --> 00:36:11,9
No one saw her.

950
00:36:12,017 --> 00:36:14,2
So are you ready
to face the cameras?

951
00:36:14,050 --> 00:36:15,9
His sponsors will love
the free publicity.

952
00:36:16,017 --> 00:36:18,7
Tell me, what's
ten percent of nothing?

953
00:36:18,092 --> 00:36:20,3
I saw Debra there.

954
00:36:22,030 --> 00:36:24,2
I went by the party.

955
00:36:25,097 --> 00:36:29,7
But a work call came up,
and I never made it inside.

956
00:36:29,093 --> 00:36:31,6
I didn't say anything before

957
00:36:31,085 --> 00:36:34,4
because I told my wife
I was working late.

958
00:36:34,061 --> 00:36:38,5
When I was driving away,
I saw Debra outside Ty's window.

959
00:36:38,078 --> 00:36:41,1
So you admit you were
there that night.

960
00:36:41,036 --> 00:36:43,8
Yeah, and so was Debra.

961
00:36:44,003 --> 00:36:45,1
That's the proof
you need, right?

962
00:36:45,037 --> 00:36:46,7
CHLOE: That's
the proof we need.

963
00:36:46,099 --> 00:36:48,9
We have a sworn statement
from Ronnie Hillman

964
00:36:49,012 --> 00:36:50,4
saying that you hired the victim

965
00:36:50,062 --> 00:36:52,4
to make a sex tape with
Ty to blackmail him.

966
00:36:52,062 --> 00:36:54,0
I just needed to place
you at the scene.

967
00:36:54,029 --> 00:36:55,7
LUCIFER: Yeah, see,
that's why I don't lie.

968
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:57,6
It's so hard to keep track
of who knows what.

969
00:36:57,084 --> 00:36:59,5
It's not true.

970
00:36:59,071 --> 00:37:02,0
I only want what's
best for you, Ty.

971
00:37:02,022 --> 00:37:03,6
You know, I still
don't understand.

972
00:37:03,084 --> 00:37:05,5
Why is it my own agent
would want to blackmail me?

973
00:37:05,072 --> 00:37:07,8
Because he thought eventually
you were gonna leave him.

974
00:37:08,006 --> 00:37:09,7
What, because I took one meeting
with another agency?

975
00:37:10,098 --> 00:37:12,1
Joe...

976
00:37:12,039 --> 00:37:13,6
I only did that
to make Debra happy.

977
00:37:13,090 --> 00:37:15,0
But even though
you'd broken up,

978
00:37:15,023 --> 00:37:16,5
he knew you'd get
back together,

979
00:37:16,073 --> 00:37:19,1
so he decided to strike first,
get some leverage.

980
00:37:19,032 --> 00:37:22,5
If he left me,
I would be ruined.

981
00:37:22,074 --> 00:37:24,2
I mean,
do you understand?

982
00:37:24,041 --> 00:37:26,0
He is my Brady, my Manning.

983
00:37:26,024 --> 00:37:28,3
But Ali wasn't cut out
for this sort of thing, was she?

984
00:37:28,058 --> 00:37:29,7
She didn't want
to give you the video.

985
00:37:29,099 --> 00:37:31,3
Stupid bitch.

986
00:37:33,050 --> 00:37:36,0
She said she realized
Ty was a good guy.

987
00:37:36,021 --> 00:37:37,6
She didn't want to go
through with it.

988
00:37:37,084 --> 00:37:40,6
Her name was Ali Thornton,
and you killed her.

989
00:37:40,084 --> 00:37:41,8
For what?

990
00:37:42,009 --> 00:37:44,0
Greed? Ego?

991
00:37:44,026 --> 00:37:45,3
I didn't want to hurt her.

992
00:37:45,059 --> 00:37:47,8
I just wanted her phone. And...

993
00:37:48,010 --> 00:37:49,7
(Joe sighs)

994
00:37:54,035 --> 00:37:56,2
But I squeezed too hard.

995
00:37:58,006 --> 00:37:59,0
I'm done.

996
00:37:59,023 --> 00:38:01,1
Forget this.
I'm out of here.

997
00:38:06,007 --> 00:38:08,4
(gasps)

998
00:38:08,062 --> 00:38:09,9
Did I squeeze too hard?

999
00:38:11,074 --> 00:38:13,9
How did you...?

1000
00:38:14,012 --> 00:38:15,2
What did...?

1001
00:38:15,046 --> 00:38:17,2
Lucifer, what are you doing?

1002
00:38:17,046 --> 00:38:19,4
Finally focusing my
anger where it belongs.

1003
00:38:19,063 --> 00:38:20,5
Lucifer...

1004
00:38:24,005 --> 00:38:27,2
(chuckles)

1005
00:38:27,043 --> 00:38:29,6
Yes, of course.

1006
00:38:29,085 --> 00:38:31,4
Your turn, Detective.

1007
00:38:31,064 --> 00:38:34,7
(sirens wailing,
radio chatter)

1008
00:38:40,073 --> 00:38:43,1
I still can't believe
Joe did this.

1009
00:38:43,040 --> 00:38:46,7
I wasn't ever gonna
leave him, you know that?

1010
00:38:46,095 --> 00:38:48,4
Definitely gonna leave him now.

1011
00:38:48,061 --> 00:38:50,0
But you know what,
you, uh...

1012
00:38:50,028 --> 00:38:51,9
you stayed good
to your word, Lucifer.

1013
00:38:52,012 --> 00:38:53,1
Thank you.

1014
00:38:53,033 --> 00:38:56,0
Yes, well, now you owe me one.

1015
00:38:58,087 --> 00:39:00,9
DEBRA:
Ty!

1016
00:39:01,013 --> 00:39:02,5
Ty! Ty!

1017
00:39:04,046 --> 00:39:05,8
Oh, my baby.

1018
00:39:06,005 --> 00:39:07,1
Oh, my God, I'm
so glad to see you.

1019
00:39:07,034 --> 00:39:09,4
- Oh.
- You are?

1020
00:39:09,064 --> 00:39:10,9
Yes, you are
crazy, baby.

1021
00:39:11,018 --> 00:39:12,9
- But you're my crazy,
you hear me?
- Yeah?

1022
00:39:14,097 --> 00:39:17,1
Warms the cockles,
doesn't it?

1023
00:39:18,094 --> 00:39:20,2
So, Detective,

1024
00:39:20,048 --> 00:39:21,9
looks like you've
solved another case

1025
00:39:22,019 --> 00:39:22,9
because of me.

1026
00:39:23,019 --> 00:39:24,7
I solved this case despite you.

1027
00:39:24,098 --> 00:39:26,7
What? What about the
cell phone I found?

1028
00:39:26,099 --> 00:39:28,1
That was key evidence.

1029
00:39:28,032 --> 00:39:29,7
Evidence you
almost destroyed.

1030
00:39:29,099 --> 00:39:32,2
I got you the leverage
you needed to crack Ronnie.

1031
00:39:32,049 --> 00:39:34,5
You co-opted a sting operation
for your own gain.

1032
00:39:34,079 --> 00:39:36,8
And I solved another crime.

1033
00:39:37,004 --> 00:39:39,2
Identity theft.
(chuckles)

1034
00:39:39,050 --> 00:39:42,2
Come on, admit it--
we solved this one together.

1035
00:39:42,050 --> 00:39:44,7
Or are you too egotistical
to acknowledge my help?

1036
00:39:46,084 --> 00:39:49,3
Okay, yeah, you didn't
completely destroy the case.

1037
00:39:49,055 --> 00:39:51,6
So you can stop blaming
yourself, great.

1038
00:39:51,089 --> 00:39:53,0
Whatever do you mean?

1039
00:39:54,085 --> 00:39:57,3
The whole reason you tried
to prove Ty's innocence?

1040
00:39:57,052 --> 00:39:59,2
Was to catch the true culprit.

1041
00:40:01,031 --> 00:40:02,8
Yeah, sure.

1042
00:40:07,003 --> 00:40:09,1
LUCIFER: So I decided
not to punish myself.

1043
00:40:09,032 --> 00:40:10,7
Yourself?

1044
00:40:10,099 --> 00:40:13,1
Well, my fake self.

1045
00:40:13,032 --> 00:40:14,4
The person
I'd kidnapped.

1046
00:40:14,066 --> 00:40:16,7
I decided not
to beat him up.

1047
00:40:16,099 --> 00:40:19,2
(sighs) You were right,
I was, um...

1048
00:40:19,041 --> 00:40:20,8
(sighs loudly with satisfaction)
What's the word?

1049
00:40:21,008 --> 00:40:22,5
Displacing?

1050
00:40:22,075 --> 00:40:25,5
...displacing my anger
and frustration on Luci-phony,

1051
00:40:25,075 --> 00:40:28,6
because the right person wasn't
being punished for Ali's death.

1052
00:40:28,084 --> 00:40:30,6
And who was the right person?

1053
00:40:30,084 --> 00:40:33,3
Well, the sleazy
agent, of course.

1054
00:40:33,051 --> 00:40:35,6
Ah, yeah.

1055
00:40:35,085 --> 00:40:38,8
Of all the cities in
the world, Lucifer,

1056
00:40:39,010 --> 00:40:41,5
why did you decide
to come to Los Angeles?

1057
00:40:41,073 --> 00:40:43,5
Well, the same reason
as everyone else.

1058
00:40:43,073 --> 00:40:45,2
Uh, the weather,
porn stars,

1059
00:40:45,048 --> 00:40:47,0
Mexican food-- mm!

1060
00:40:47,027 --> 00:40:48,7
Mmm.

1061
00:40:48,098 --> 00:40:50,5
You know, you say... you
say people are phony here,

1062
00:40:50,078 --> 00:40:54,5
but I think people come here
to reinvent themselves.

1063
00:40:54,078 --> 00:40:56,5
And I think that's
why you're here.

1064
00:40:56,078 --> 00:40:58,5
To reinvent yourself.

1065
00:40:58,079 --> 00:41:01,0
Why would I mess
with perfection?

1066
00:41:02,087 --> 00:41:05,2
You like working with
the detective, don't you?

1067
00:41:08,009 --> 00:41:09,9
I told you, I'm good
at punishing people--

1068
00:41:10,013 --> 00:41:12,6
nay, I'm the best
at punishing bad people.

1069
00:41:12,088 --> 00:41:15,0
I didn't enjoy it when
my father forced me to,

1070
00:41:15,022 --> 00:41:17,0
but now that it's
on my own terms,

1071
00:41:17,022 --> 00:41:19,0
it's downright delightful.

1072
00:41:19,022 --> 00:41:21,0
Yeah, well, I think
you don't just enjoy

1073
00:41:21,023 --> 00:41:23,0
punishing the bad guys.

1074
00:41:23,023 --> 00:41:25,0
I think you're starting
to like seeking justice

1075
00:41:25,023 --> 00:41:27,0
for the good ones.

1076
00:41:30,040 --> 00:41:31,4
Like Ali.

1077
00:41:31,065 --> 00:41:32,7
(Lucifer scoffs)

1078
00:41:34,086 --> 00:41:36,3
It's another reason
to hate L.A.--

1079
00:41:36,057 --> 00:41:38,0
all this self-
indulgent therapy.

1080
00:41:38,024 --> 00:41:39,2
You should be ashamed.

1081
00:41:39,045 --> 00:41:40,5
You're doing it again.

1082
00:41:40,079 --> 00:41:41,7
What?

1083
00:41:41,091 --> 00:41:43,3
Displacing.

1084
00:41:43,058 --> 00:41:45,3
No, I'm not.

1085
00:41:45,058 --> 00:41:46,8
And that's denial.

1086
00:41:47,008 --> 00:41:49,1
That's a river in Africa.

1087
00:41:49,034 --> 00:41:51,1
(chuckles)

1088
00:41:51,034 --> 00:41:53,5
♪♪

1089
00:42:00,047 --> 00:42:02,9
♪ You looked so good at first ♪

1090
00:42:03,018 --> 00:42:06,4
♪ When I didn't know your name ♪

1091
00:42:06,069 --> 00:42:09,6
♪ But you took me by surprise ♪

1092
00:42:09,086 --> 00:42:13,9
♪ You made me feel so strange ♪

1093
00:42:14,020 --> 00:42:17,4
♪ Ooh... ♪

1094
00:42:21,016 --> 00:42:24,2
♪ Ooh... ♪

